How Google Works by Eric Schmidt and Jonathan
Rosenberg

2
00:00:13,410 --> 00:00:19,810
Eric Schmidt was the CEO of Google for ten
years. He became the CEO in 2001. At that

3
00:00:19,809 --> 00:00:24,428
point it was a successful three year old internet
start-up, but was already preparing to compete

4
00:00:24,428 --> 00:00:28,729
with the giant Microsoft.
Google was different to other places Schmidt

5
00:00:28,730 --> 00:00:35,049
had worked. Even as CEO he had to share his
office. The company was growing in size and

6
00:00:35,049 --> 00:00:39,069
in 2002 Jonathan Rosenberg joined as Head
of Products.

7
00:00:39,070 --> 00:00:44,289
The company’s early principles consisted
of focusing on the user, hiring as many great

8
00:00:44,289 --> 00:00:49,329
software engineers as they could and give
those engineers freedom. Google was managed

9
00:00:49,329 --> 00:00:52,719
