77
00:06:26,310 --> 00:06:30,329
Communications
Effective leaders today share information

78
00:06:30,329 --> 00:06:35,990
rather than keeping it to themselves. As a
leader, knowing the details is key too. This

79
00:06:35,990 --> 00:06:41,050
requires asking the right questions. An environment
must be created where tough questions can

80
00:06:41,050 --> 00:06:45,759
be asked and the truth can always be told
– even when the truth is not good news.

81
00:06:45,759 --> 00:06:51,209
When it comes to email, aim to respond quickly.
As a result you’ll be more likely to be

82
00:06:51,209 --> 00:06:56,169
included in decisions and discussions that
are important. Emails should be clear and

83
00:06:56,170 --> 00:07:01,610
to the point. There shouldn’t be any content
in there that people can skip.

84
00:07:01,610 --> 00:07:06,040
Innovation
iOS, the operating system that runs on Apple’s

85
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:11,400
iPhones and Android, Google’s OS that runs
on many other smart phones are two innovative

86
00:07:11,399 --> 00:07:16,519
products created by two of the most innovative
companies around today. However, whilst similar

87
00:07:16,519 --> 00:07:21,299
in some ways, they highlight two differing
approaches to innovation.

88
00:07:21,300 --> 00:07:26,110
Android is open-source. Anyone can use the
software’s code for free and anyone can

89
00:07:26,110 --> 00:07:31,090
sell apps that run on Android devices without
approval. Apple’s approach is different

90
00:07:31,089 --> 00:07:35,259
with iOS code being closed and apps requiring
approval.

91
00:07:35,259 --> 00:07:40,860
Google defines an innovative product as being
new, surprising and radically useful – Google’s

92
00:07:40,860 --> 00:07:45,189
driverless cars being a textbook example,
but how does a company become innovative?

93
00:07:45,189 --> 00:07:51,089
The environment needs to be right. It should
encourage people smart enough to come up with

94
00:07:51,089 --> 00:07:54,789
new ideas and also encourage those who want
to join that individual.

95
00:07:54,790 --> 00:08:02,220
The company focus should be on the user. In
2004, Google bought a start-up called Keyhole.

96
00:08:02,220 --> 00:08:06,560
Using Keyhole’s technology they launched
Google Earth. It did not offer any direct

97
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:11,870
impact to the company financially, but it
was a tremendous hit with the user.

98
00:08:11,870 --> 00:08:16,389
Thinking big is essential and provides the
advantage of giving smart creatives more freedom.

99
00:08:16,389 --> 00:08:22,550
Big challenges also tend to attract big talent.
Google also runs a program where its engineers

100
00:08:22,550 --> 00:08:28,139
can spend 20% of their time working on whatever
they want. It has spawned some valuable features

101
00:08:28,139 --> 00:08:33,250
from Google’s search engine suggesting search
queries as you type, to adding bus and train

102
00:08:33,250 --> 00:08:38,820
information on Google maps.
The current age is one where many industries

103
00:08:38,820 --> 00:08:43,930
are feeling the effect of the disruption caused
by technology. Gone are the days where people

104
00:08:43,929 --> 00:08:48,809
only watch video on a television for example.
There are economic impacts to these industries

105
00:08:48,809 --> 00:08:53,449
due to this, so what can we do to survive
this period?

106
00:08:53,450 --> 00:08:57,060
Businesses should utilise new platforms to
their advantage which will enable them to

107
00:08:57,059 --> 00:09:03,028
produce great products. The social web, where
users can share things and talk about them

108
00:09:03,028 --> 00:09:07,350
has emerged. Companies should ensure that
their products and services compliment the

109
00:09:07,350 --> 00:09:10,360
social web.
Think not only about your company, but the

110
00:09:10,360 --> 00:09:15,990
future as well. What could be true five years
from now and how will it affect the landscape?

111
00:09:15,990 --> 00:09:21,899
Schmidt and Rosenberg believe that with enough
data and ability, any challenge can be solved.

112
00:09:21,899 --> 00:09:26,600
Computers will continue to make lives easier
and better but for yet more people. Speed

113
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:30,970
will continue to increase, as will the amount
of collaboration thanks to the free flow of

114
00:09:30,970 --> 00:09:36,570
information. The future is bright as technology
will transform practically every industry

115
00:09:36,570 --> 00:09:37,290
or field.

